race_comments: Carl Edwards won the Bojangles' Southern 500, his 25th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory and first at Darlington Raceway. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 10 (backup car) and No. 25 (rear gear change).

race_name: Food City 500 in Support of Steve Byrnes and Stand Up to Cancer
race_comments: Matt Kenseth won the Food City 500 in Support of Steve Byrnes at Bristol Motor Speedway, his 32nd victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and fourth at the track. Prior to the start of the race, the No. 95 dropped to the rear of the field for unapproved adjustments.

Joey Logano won the IRWIN Tools Night Race, his 11th win in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and his second at Bristol Motor Speedway. No cars dropped to the rear of the field prior to the start of the race.

Denny Hamlin won the STP 500 at Martinsville Speedway, his 25th victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and fifth at the track. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated:  #13 (transmission), #42 (driver change) and #51 (backup car).

Jeff Gordon won the Goody's Headache Relief Shot 500, his 93rd career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory and ninth at Martinsville Speedway. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 5 and No. 14 (backup car).

Kurt Busch won the Toyota Owners 400 at Richmond International Raceway, his 26th victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and second at the track. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: #23 (driver change), #35 (transmission change), #30 (engine change).
Matt Kenseth won the Federated Auto Parts 400, his 35th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory.

Brad Keselowski won the Auto Club 400 at Auto Club Speedway, his 17th victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and first at the track. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated:  #55 (backup car).

Denny Hamlin won the myAFibRisk.com 400, his 26th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 34 (transmission change).

Kyle Busch won the Ford EcoBoost 400, his 34th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars 

dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 38 (transmission change).
Jimmie Johnson won the SpongeBob SquarePants 400, his 73rd victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and third at the track. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Joey Logano won the Hollywood Casino 400, his 13th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 13 (backup car).

Kevin Harvick won the Kobalt 400 at Las Vegas Motor Speedway, his 29th victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: #18, 24 (backup car).

Jimmie Johnson won the Duck Commander 500 at Texas Motor Speedway, his 72nd victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated:  #31 (engine change).

Jimmie Johnson won the AAA Texas 500, his 75th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 98 (engine change) and 14 (missed driver introductions).

race_name: Quaker State 400 Presented by Advance Auto Parts
race_comments:
Kyle Busch won the Quaker State 400 presented by Advance Auto Parts, his 31st career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, 
no cars dropped to the rear of the field.
Dale Earnhardt Jr. won the GEICO 500 at Talladega Superspeedway, his 24th victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Joey Logano won the CampingWorld.com 500, his 14th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 10 (transmission repair), No. 14 (unapproved adjustments) and No. 51 (repairs).

Kevin Harvick won the CampingWorld.com 500 at Phoenix International Raceway, his 30th victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and seventh at Phoenix. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated:  #47 (engine change).
Dale Earnhardt Jr. won the Quicken Loans Race for Heroes 500, his 26th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory.

Kyle Busch won the Toyota/Save Mart 350, his 30th career NASCAR Sprint Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 27, 46 (engine change).

Jimmie Johnson won the FedEx 400 benefiting Autism Speaks, his 74th career NASCAR Sprint Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 88 (changing rear gear).

Kevin Harvick won the AAA 400, his 31st career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 78 (unapproved adjustments).
Matt Kenseth won the Sprint Unlimited at Daytona International Speedway, his first victory in the preseason event. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear under penalty.

Dale Earnhardt Jr. won the Budweiser Duel at Daytona #1 at Daytona International Speedway, his fourth victory in the Daytona 500 qualifying event. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field: #15, 23, 46 (backup car), 88 (failed post qualifying inspection).

Jimmie Johnson won the Budweiser Duel at Daytona #2 at Daytona International Speedway, his second victory in the Daytona 500 qualifying event. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field: #31 (engine change) #32, 10, 26, 44 (backup car), 11 (failed post qualifying inspection).

Joey Logano won the Daytona 500 at Daytona International Speedway, his ninth victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and first Daytona 500. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: #18, #41 (Driver Change), #3, #6, #9, #10, #31, #32, #34, #42, #47, #83 (Backup Car).
Dale Earnhardt Jr. won the Coke Zero 400, his 25th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Jimmie Johnson won the Folds of Honor QuikTrip 500 at Atlanta Motor Speedway, his 71st victory in the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series and fourth at Atlanta. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: #4 (engine change), #14 (missed driver introductions), #33 (driver change).

race_name: Crown Royal Presents the Jeff Kyle 400 at the Brickyard
race_comments:
Kyle Busch won the Crown Royal Presents the Jeff Kyle 400 at the Brickyard, his 33rd career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the 

start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Kurt Busch won the Quicken Loans 400, his 27th career NASCAR Sprint Series victory. The race was shortened due to inclement weather. Prior to the start 
of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 23 (engine change).

Matt Kenseth won the Pure Michigan 400, his 34th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 3, 33 (engine change); No. 18 (backup car).

Kyle Busch won the 5-hour ENERGY 301, his 32nd career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory, and second at New Hampshire Motor Speedway. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Matt Kenseth won the SYLVANIA 300, his 36th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 32 (Rear Gear Change).
Joey Logano won the CHEEZ-It 355 at The Glen, his 10th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.
Greg Biffle and Clint Bowyer won the two segments in the Sprint Showdown.

Denny Hamlin won the NASCAR Sprint All-Star Race, his first win in the annual non-points race. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 10 (engine change).
Carl Edwards won the Coca-Cola 600, his 24th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory.
Joey Logano won the Bank of America 500, his 12th career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory.

Martin Truex Jr. won the Axalta 'We Paint Winners' 400, his third career NASCAR Sprint Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 22 (changing rear gear).

Matt Kenseth won the Windows 10 400, his 33rd career NASCAR Sprint Cup Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 26 (backup car); No. 31 (rear gear).
